the position. White's position is worse, so he cannot play tactical
moves and change the situation. As Fischer used to say, tactics
flow from a superior position. The best move for White is to
capture the strong knight on d5 and then try to equalize the
game.} (30.Bxd5 $5 exd5 $15) 30...Bxe6 31.Bxd5 e3 $3 {This is a very
strong and forcing reply White has missed. Do you remember Fischer's
quote: 'It is very natural to see a good tactical blow from Black
because they have a better position"? By the way, this is the
only strong move that gives Black a better position. If a player
misses such moves, his advantage will slip away. Ex-World Champion
Anand is a very strong player and rarely misses such opportunities.} 32.Bxe3
